.TH "pwmchip_add_with_polarity" 9 "pwmchip_add_with_polarity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pwmchip_add_with_polarity \- register a new PWM chip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pwmchip_add_with_polarity
.BI "(struct pwm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "enum pwm_polarity polarity "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
the PWM chip to add
.IP "polarity" 12
initial polarity of PWM channels
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register a new PWM chip. If chip->base < 0 then a dynamically assigned base
will be used. The initial polarity for all channels is specified by the
\fIpolarity\fP parameter.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
